docs.abstract: Lawmakers will try to assemble immigration legislation that can garner 60 votes as the Senate undertakes an exceedingly rare open-ended debate.
docs.snippet: Lawmakers will try to assemble immigration legislation that can garner 60 votes as the Senate undertakes an exceedingly rare open-ended debate.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With the fate of hundreds of thousands of young, undocumented immigrants in the balance, the Senate on Monday began an open-ended debate on immigration — an exceedingly rare step that, in effect, will allow senators to attempt to build a bill from scratch on the Senate floor.

headline.main: Senate Begins ‘Wild’ Week of Debate on Immigration, Outcome Unknown
headline.print_headline: Senators Begin a Debate to Create an Immigration Bill From Scratch
